&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/2255&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/2255&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4539&quot; title=&quot;StreamThread is not correctly creating  StandbyTasks&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-4539&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-4539&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: NPE in StreamThread when creating StandbyTasks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Tasks that don&apos;t have any `StateStore`s wont have a `StandbyTask`, so `createStandbyTask` can return `null`. We need to check for this in `StandbyTaskCreator.createTask(...)`&lt;/p&gt;

